Florida Panthers Fire Coach DeBoer After Last-Place Finish in NHL East

-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 
2011-04-10T16:07:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-10/florida-panthers-fire-coach-deboer-after-last-place-finish-in-nhl-east.html
The Florida Panthers fired coach
Peter DeBoer after the team finished last in the  National Hockey
League ’s Eastern Conference.  DeBoer, 42, went 103-107 in three seasons with the
Panthers, his first head-coaching position in the NHL. The team
finished 30-40 in the 2010-11 regular season.  “We felt strongly that it was the right time to make a
change,” Panthers General Manager Dale Tallon said in a
statement on the team’s website.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dex McLuskey at 
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net  